{"lemma":"رَجْعَةٍ","slug":"رَجْعَةٍ","root":"ر.ج.ع","root_slug":"ر-ج-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14879","n14890","n14914","n14891","n14892"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14879","headword_ar":"رجّعهُ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojiyEN","text_ar":"تَرْجِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to return, go back, come back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert, again and again,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time; sent back, turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, again and again,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time; made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to go,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"move, repeatedly to and fro; so to go and come; to reciprocate: he repeated it; iterated it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reiterated it: he reproduced it: he renewed it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~adahu","text_ar":"رَدَّدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) [All these significations are well known, as pertaining to the two verbs here mentioned, and of frequent occurrence in classical and postclassical writings: and hence several phrases here following.] ―         -b2-  See 1, last quarter of the paragraph, in five places. ―         -b3-  Hence, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arojiyEu","text_ar":"التَّرْجِيعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^a*aAni","text_ar":"فِى الاَذَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) because the two professions of the faith [for which see the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAnN","text_ar":"اَذَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are uttered in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*An","text_ar":"اذان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or call to prayer] in a low voice [and then repeated in a high voice]; (Mgh;) [for] this phrase means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The repeating the two professions of the faith in a raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loud, voice, after uttering them in a low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faint, voice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lowering of the voice in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*An","text_ar":"اذان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in uttering the two professions of the faith, and then raising it in uttering them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~E fiY A^a*aAnihi","text_ar":"رجّع فِى اَذَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he uttered the two professions of the faith in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*An","text_ar":"اذان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"once to repeat them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb: [but this is a strange explanation; and probably corrupted by a copyist: it seems that, instead of “ to repeat them, ” we should read “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and repeated them."},{"kind":"text","text":"”]) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arojiyEu","text_ar":"التَّرْجِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojiyEu AlS~awoti","text_ar":"تَرْجِيعُ الصَّوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The act of quavering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trilling; rapidly repeating many times one very short note,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each note of a piece;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a general characteristic of Arabian chanting and singing and piping, and often continued throughout the whole performance;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the reiterating"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarodiyd","text_ar":"تَرْدِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the voice in the throat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is done in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is practised in reading"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reciting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other performances, of such as are accompanied with quavering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trilling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mutual approximation of the various kinds of movements in the voice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"'Abd-Allah Ibn-Mughaffal, in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trjyE","text_ar":"ترجيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", by the prolonging of the voice, in reading, or reciting, imitated the like of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=A A=A A=A","text_ar":"ا=ا ا=ا ا=ا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~E AlHamaAmu fiY","text_ar":"رجّع الحَمَامُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginaAy^ihi","text_ar":"غِنَايِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pigeons quavered in their singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstrjE","text_ar":"استرجع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~E","text_ar":"رجّع"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyru fiY $iqo$iqatihi","text_ar":"البَعِيرُ فِى شِقْشِقَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel brayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reiterated his voice, in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$q$qp","text_ar":"شقشقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bursa faucium"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~Et Aln~aAqapu fiY HaniynihaA","text_ar":"رجّعت النَّاقَةُ فِى حَنِينِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel interrupted her yearning cry to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, her young one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly repeated it, and did so again and again"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~Et Alqawosu","text_ar":"رجّعت القَوْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bow made a sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the vibration of its string;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the sound so made is a repeated sound]. (AHn.) ―         -b5-  See also 4. ―         -b6-  And see 10."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","S","K","KT","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n14890","headword_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of un. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A return; a single act of returning, of going back, coming back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwEN","text_ar":"رُجُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning to the present state of existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) So in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yuw^ominu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يُوْمِنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlr~ajoEapi","text_ar":"بِالرَّجْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one believes in the returning to the present state of existence after death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K. *) This was a tenet of some of the Arabs in the Time of Ignorance, and of a sect of Muslim innovators, and of a sect of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDap","text_ar":"رَافِضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", who say that 'Alee the son of Aboo-Tálib is concealing himself in the clouds, to come forth when he shall be summoned to do so. (L.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"homeward course, of a military expedition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badoA^apN","text_ar":"بَدْاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (T and Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdA^","text_ar":"بدا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return of a party of warriors to war after their having come back from an expedition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Nh, Mgh, Msb, K,) but the former is the more chaste, (S, Msb, TA,) though the latter is mentioned before the former in the K, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man's returning to his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restoring her to himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking her back by marriage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the marriage-state, after having divorced her;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning of the divorcer to the divorced woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking back to marriage a woman who has been divorced, but not by an absolutely-separating sentence, without a new contract."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EalaY A@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"لَهُ عَلَى ا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a right of returning to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking back, his wife after having divorced her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamoliku Alr~ajoEapa EalaY zawojatihi","text_ar":"يَمْلِكُ الرَّجْعَةَ عَلَى زَوْجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He possesses the right of returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tal~aqa fulaAnN fulaAnapa TalaAqFA yamoliku fiyhi Alr~ajoEapa","text_ar":"طَلَّقَ فُلَانٌ فُلَانَةَ طَلَاقًا يَمْلِكُ فِيهِ الرَّجْعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a man divorced such a woman by a divorce in which he possessed the right of returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  Also the former, (S, Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEapN","text_ar":"رُجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaY","text_ar":"رُجْعَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is also originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEN","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEapN","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajuwEapN","text_ar":"رَجُوعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the last of these is allowable, (TA,) [being an inf. n. used in the sense of a pass. part. n.,] (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an epistle. (S, Msb, * K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo jaA='a","text_ar":"هَلْ جَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapu kitaAbika","text_ar":"رَجْعَةُ كِتَابِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnuhu","text_ar":"رُجْعَانُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hath the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of thine epistle come:?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosaltu A_ilayoka famaA jaA='aniY rujoEaY","text_ar":"اَرْسَلتُ اـِلَيْكَ فَمَا جَا=ءَنِى رُجْعَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risaAlatiY","text_ar":"رِسَالَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sent to thee, and the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of my epistle came not to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEuhaA","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK Ealayoka","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAna mino marojuwEi","text_ar":"مَا كَانَ مِنْ مَرْجُوعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What was"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the purport]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of such a one to thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~i$oq","text_ar":"الرِّشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEu","text_ar":"رَجْعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is returned against,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in opposition to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in reply to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the simultaneous discharge of a number of arrows in a particular direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","A","Nh","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n14914","headword_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ","root":"rjf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zalozalapN","text_ar":"زَلْزَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Commotion, agitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"convulsion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violent commotion"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an earthquake;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a violent earthquake:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vehement cry from heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in vii. 76:) or it signifies, in the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any punishment that befalls a people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n14891","headword_ar":"رُجْعَةٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the latter half of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14892","headword_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit, obtained by the expenditure of the price of camels sold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotajaEa","text_ar":"اِرْتَجَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels taken in exchange for other camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is taken in the place, and with the price, of two:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"younglings, of camels, which are purchased from the market with the price of others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken from the market in exchange for others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, as Khálid says, the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return obtained by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing bad camels into the market and taking back good ones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return obtained by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing in males and taking back females:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [the words which I have here twice inserted in brackets are perhaps not necessary to complete the sense intended, as will be seen at the close of this sentence; but they seem to be required in the opinion of SM, for he has"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1041},{"kind":"text","text":"immediately added the further explanation which here next follows, and which is also, but less fully, given by J, immediately after the first explanation in this paragraph:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a similar meaning in relation to the poor-rates; being applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels taken by the collector of the poor-rates older or younger than those which their owner is bound to give:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels which are purchased by the Arabs of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in exchange-for others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of their own breeding nor bearing their marks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA, [see 8:]) IB says that the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujaEN","text_ar":"رُجَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that it was said to a tribe of the Arabs, “ By what means have your beasts become many? ” and they answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoSaAnaA A^abuwnaA","text_ar":"اَوْصَانَا اَبُونَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~ujaEi waAlr~ujaEi","text_ar":"بِالنُّجَعِ وَالرُّجَعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but Th says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAln~ijaEi wAlr~ijaEi","text_ar":"بالنِّجَعِ والرِّجَعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": [both are probably correct; for it seems that the original forms are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ujaE","text_ar":"النُّجَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ijaE","text_ar":"الرِّجَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that, in one case, the latter is assimilated to the former; in the other, accord. to a usage less common, the former to the latter:] accord. to Th, the meaning is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our father charged us with the seekings after herbage in the places thereof, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the selling the old and weak beasts and purchasing others in a state of youthful vigour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to another explanation, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the selling males and purchasing females:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus explained,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaEN","text_ar":"رِجَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be an inf. n. (TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa naAqapF","text_ar":"رَجَعَ نَاقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiyEa","text_ar":"رَجِيعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any return, profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, accruing from a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obtained by the sale"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exchange thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEN","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ato rijoEapu AlD~iyaAEi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتْ رِجْعَةُ الضِّيَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increase, accruing to the owner of the lands came,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrived."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birijoEapK HasanapK","text_ar":"بِرِجْعَةٍ حَسَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one brought a good thing which he had purchased in the place of a bad thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of a thing that was inferior to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mataAEN lahu marojuwEN","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَتَاعٌ لَهُ مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a commodity for which there will be a return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~apN lahaA marojuwEN","text_ar":"دَابَّةٌ لَهَا مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beast that may be sold after having been used."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Isbahánee.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa lih`*aA AlbayoEi marojuwEN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِهٰذَا البَيْعِ مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not be, any return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, for this sale."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An argument,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allegation, by which one rebuts in a litigation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispute; a proof; an evidence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Mgh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}